In the TV show "How I Met Your Mother," Marshall convinces Lily to come back to New York after she leaves to pursue an art career in San Francisco. In Season 1, Episode 3, titled "Sweet Taste of Liberty," Lily impulsively leaves New York to pursue an art fellowship in San Francisco, leaving Marshall devastated. However, after a week apart, Marshall travels to San Francisco and convinces Lily to come back to New York with him. He tells her that he can't imagine his life without her and promises to support her art career while also pursuing his own dreams. His heartfelt plea convinces Lily to return with him, and the couple reconciles.